      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is primarily supported by the principle that the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding of the text at the time it was ratified, ensuring stability and preventing arbitrary judicial overreach. Proponents argue that this approach respects the democratic will of the Founders and avoids judges imposing their own personal values or policies onto the law. By sticking to the original meaning, originalists believe they constrain judicial power and maintain the separation of powers, allowing elected representatives to adapt the Constitution through amendment when society's needs change. This method aims to preserve the document as a fair, enduring framework that applies consistently across generations.",
